  • Package model

    • Class model.Application

      class Application extends Object implements Serializable
      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • applicationId
          String applicationId
          Unique identifier for the application. Generated automatically by the system.
        • opportunityId
          String opportunityId
          ID of the internship opportunity being applied for.
        • placementAcceptanceDate
          LocalDateTime placementAcceptanceDate
          Date and time when the placement was accepted by the student. Null if placement not yet accepted.
        • placementAccepted
          boolean placementAccepted
          Flag indicating if the student has accepted the internship placement. Only applicable when status is SUCCESSFUL.
        • representativeComments
          String representativeComments
          Comments or feedback from the company representative. Optional field for rejection reasons or approval notes.
        • status
          ApplicationStatus status
          Current status of the application. Default: PENDING
        • statusUpdateDate
          LocalDateTime statusUpdateDate
          Date and time when the application status was last updated. Null if never updated after submission.
        • studentId
          String studentId
          User ID of the student who submitted this application.
        • submissionDate
          LocalDateTime submissionDate
          Date and time when the application was submitted.

    • Class model.CompanyRepresentative

      class CompanyRepresentative extends User implements Serializable
      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • companyName
          String companyName
          Name of the company the representative works for.
        • department
          String department
          Department within the company. Example: Human Resources, Engineering, Marketing
        • internshipIds
          List<String> internshipIds
          List of internship opportunity IDs created by this representative. Maximum size is MAX_INTERNSHIPS (5).
        • isAuthorized
          boolean isAuthorized
          Authorization status indicating if the representative can login. Must be set to true by Career Center Staff before account is active.
        • position
          String position
          Job position/title of the representative. Example: HR Manager, Recruitment Specialist

    • Class model.InternshipOpportunity

      class InternshipOpportunity extends Object implements Serializable
      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • closingDate
          LocalDate closingDate
          Date when applications close for this internship. Applications cannot be submitted after this date.
        • companyName
          String companyName
          Name of the company offering the internship.
        • description
          String description
          Detailed description of the internship role and responsibilities.
        • filledSlots
          int filledSlots
          Number of slots that have been confirmed by students. Internship becomes FILLED when filledSlots equals totalSlots.
        • level
          InternshipLevel level
          Level of the internship (BASIC, INTERMEDIATE, ADVANCED). Determines student eligibility based on year of study.
        • openingDate
          LocalDate openingDate
          Date when applications open for this internship.
        • opportunityId
          String opportunityId
          Unique identifier for the internship opportunity. Generated automatically by the system.
        • preferredMajor
          String preferredMajor
          Preferred major for applicants. Can be specific (e.g., "CSC", "EEE") or "Any" for all majors.
        • representativeId
          String representativeId
          User ID of the company representative who created this opportunity.
        • status
          InternshipStatus status
          Current status of the internship opportunity. Flow: PENDING → APPROVED → FILLED (or REJECTED)
        • title
          String title
          Title of the internship position. Example: "Software Engineering Intern", "Data Analyst Intern"
        • totalSlots
          int totalSlots
          Total number of available slots for this internship. Maximum value is MAX_SLOTS (10).
        • visible
          boolean visible
          Visibility flag indicating if students can see this opportunity. Can be toggled by company representative. Only affects APPROVED internships (PENDING/REJECTED never visible).

    • Class model.Student

      class Student extends User implements Serializable
      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • acceptedPlacementId
          String acceptedPlacementId
          ID of the accepted internship placement, if any. Null if no placement has been accepted yet.
        • applicationIds
          List<String> applicationIds
          List of application IDs for internships this student has applied for. Maximum size is MAX_APPLICATIONS (3).
        • major
          String major
          Student's major/program of study. Examples: CSC (Computer Science), EEE (Electrical Engineering), MAE (Mechanical Engineering) Used to filter internships by preferred major.
        • yearOfStudy
          int yearOfStudy
          Year of study (1, 2, 3, or 4). Determines eligibility for internship levels.

    • Class model.User

      class User extends Object implements Serializable
      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • email
          String email
          User's email address for communication.
        • name
          String name
          User's full name.
        • password
          String password
          User's password for authentication. Default password is "password" for all new users. Should be changed on first login for security.
        • role
          UserRole role
          Role of the user in the system. Determines permissions and available functionalities.
        • userId
          String userId
          Unique user identifier. Format varies by role: - Students: U followed by 7 digits and a letter (e.g., U2345123F) - Company Representatives: Company email address - Career Center Staff: NTU account

    • Class model.WithdrawalRequest

      class WithdrawalRequest extends Object implements Serializable
      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • applicationId
          String applicationId
          ID of the application being withdrawn.
        • isPlacementConfirmed
          boolean isPlacementConfirmed
          Flag indicating if this withdrawal is for a confirmed placement. True if student has already accepted the internship placement.
        • processedBy
          String processedBy
          User ID of the career center staff who processed this request. Null until request is processed.
        • processedDate
          LocalDateTime processedDate
          Date and time when the request was processed (approved or rejected). Null if still pending.
        • reason
          String reason
          Student's reason for requesting withdrawal. Required field that must be provided by the student.
        • requestDate
          LocalDateTime requestDate
          Date and time when the withdrawal request was submitted.
        • requestId
          String requestId
          Unique identifier for the withdrawal request. Generated automatically by the system.
        • staffComments
          String staffComments
          Comments from the career center staff regarding the decision. Optional field for approval notes or rejection reasons.
        • status
          ApprovalStatus status
          Current status of the withdrawal request. Default: PENDING
        • studentId
          String studentId
          User ID of the student submitting the withdrawal request.
